{"id": 5761, "title": "Ticket #5761: Avoid need to prepend ./ to Cmd in Docker Universe", "description": "<blockquote>\nInexplicably, \"./\" needs to be prepended to Cmd for Docker universe jobs.  So, \"foo.sh\" doesn't work (but that's OK in vanilla universe) but \"./foo.sh\" is fine.\n\n<p>Can we get rid of this requirement to make this behave a bit more vanilla-y?</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jul-20 10:28</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/81c3235085bc7ac54db8622a24d1af83b2eabfef\">[48807]</a></span>: Document <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5761\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5761'); return false;\" title=\"Avoid need to prepend ./ to Cmd in Docker Universe\">#5761</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jul-05 18:25</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/5621d1a72c505fac7c6d98f2b7b8d3d9ef807dd4\">[48740]</a></span>: Avoid need to prepend ./ to Cmd in Docker universe <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5761\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5761'); return false;\" title=\"Avoid need to prepend ./ to Cmd in Docker Universe\">#5761</a></span> Docker universe now supports transfer_executable = true|false and a new heuristic to set it to true if it isn't set, and the exe is an absolute path Committer: Tim Theisen  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jul-05 15:13</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/8feed139e54bfce582f9c5668da3ea5206c1e9b7\">[48738]</a></span>: Avoid need to prepend ./ to Cmd in Docker universe <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5761\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5761'); return false;\" title=\"Avoid need to prepend ./ to Cmd in Docker Universe\">#5761</a></span> Docker universe now supports transfer_executable = true|false and a new heuristic to set it to true if it isn't set, and the exe is an absolute path  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2016-Jul-20 10:44", "status": "resolved", "created": "2016-Jun-28 20:21", "fixed_version": "2016-Jun-28 20:21", "broken_version": "", "priority": "2", "subsystem": "DaemonsExecNode", "assigned_to": "gthain", "derived_from": "#5757", "creator": "bbockelm", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "bbockelm@cse.unl.edu", "due_date": ""}